{{Italic title}} The '''''Cochin State Manual''''' was a 1911 CE publication of the then-[[princely state]] of [[Cochin]], detailing the social, economic, and historical conditions of the state. It was compiled by C. Achutha Menon (1862-1937), secretary to the Devaswom of Cochin, and bore close similarity to the district manuals and gazetteers of the British Raj.<ref>{{cite book |title=The Indian Gazetteers |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DNUmAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Travancore+State+Manual%22&dq=%22Travancore+State+Manual%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=iKWJT6fZJuLy0gG62-DnCQ&ved=0CEcQ6AEwBTge |page=24 |accessdate=14 July 2015 |year=1967 |publisher=Ministry of Education, Government of India}}</ref>
==See also== * ''[[Travancore State Manual]]'' * [[Devaswom boards in Kerala]]
