{{italic title}}
The '''''Icelandic Encyclopedia A-Ö''''' is an encyclopedia in the [[Icelandic language]] published in 1990 by [[Örn og Örlygur]]. The book is in three volumes, containing about 37,000 tags and 4,500 drawings and maps, and is also the first Icelandic encyclopedia. The editors were [[Dora Hafsteinsdóttir]] and [[Sigrid Harðardóttir]]. Another printing came out in 1992.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timarit.is/view_page_init.jsp?pageId=2694698 |title=Dagur, 11.04.1991 |publisher=Timarit.is |date= |accessdate=2016-04-02}}</ref>

The book is based on the Danish [[Fakta, Gyldendals etbinds leksikon]] issued in 1988.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ismennt.is/vefir/malbjorg/kafli9.htm |title=9 |publisher=Ismennt.is |date= |accessdate=2016-04-02}}</ref> Contracts on the encyclopedia were reached in 1987 and originally planned to come out in a parallel Danish edition.

