{{italic title}}
'''''State v. Pike''''', 49 N.h. 399 (1869), is a [[criminal case]] which articulated a [[product test]] for an [[insanity defense]].<ref name=IECJ>Insanity, 2 Encyclopedia of Crime and Justice 736-40 (1983); Abraham Goldstein</ref> The court in ''[[Durham v. United States (1954)|Durham v. United States]]'' used it as the basis for what came to be known as the [[Durham rule]].<ref name=IECJ/>

